"{\n  \"missions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"M09\",\n      \"title\": \"Faces in the Ash\",\n      \"quest_giver\": {\"name\": \"Kael Ibrin\", \"affiliation\": \"Ashen Wardens\"},\n      \"description\": \"Ash fell in veils that drifted like memories trying to put themselves back together, and the Caldera’s basalt organ-pipes boomed with breath from the earth like a cathedral singing to a buried god. Pyre-Mistress Kael Ibrin pressed a soot-scented mask into Neris Quay’s hands, its filters whispering as if they already knew the taste of guilt, and set out the charge with the severity of an oath: escort a basalt caravan across pumice fields in an ash-squall, keep lungs working when masks grew few, parley with drake-tamers at the warm vents without lighting a war, and pry loose an obsidian core to tune Parliament’s truth-lamps and edge the Basilica’s ritual blades. The Wardens swore the ash remembered shapes, and this veil remembered Neris, or at least the shape of a choice once made to turn a flame backward so a law could stumble and a city could breathe longer; the wind changed and glass-ice formed on any skin that dared the air, whispering with every sting, you knew and you did it anyway. The caravan’s ropes creaked like conscience, the basalt blocks thrummed with a miner’s hymn, and the pumice fields sparkled like a field of teeth waiting for a word to bite. Drakes wheeled along the rim where warm vents breathed, their silhouettes like winged commas in an interrupted sentence, watching to see whether this crossing would be a story of bargains, or a story of blood.\",\n      \"objectives\": [\n        \"Escort a basalt caravan across pumice fields during an ash-squall while rationing masks to keep everyone breathing.\",\n        \"Negotiate with drake-tamers for safe crossing near a guarded warm vent without provoking a fight.\",\n        \"Retrieve an obsidian core suitable for ritual blades and lamp tuning from a vent-ring.\",\n        \"Protect the caravan from 